Splits the enumerable in two lists according to the given function fun.

    iex> Credo.Backports.Enum.split_with([true, false, true, true, false], &(&1))
    {[true, true, true], [false, false]}

    iex> Credo.Backports.Enum.split_with(["hello", "same", "sample"], &(String.starts_with?(&1, "he")))
    {["hello"], ["same", "sample"]}

Returns a `Options` struct for the given parameters.

    iex> Credo.CLI.Options.parse(["alice", "--debug"], ".", ["alice", "bob", "eve"], [])
    %Credo.CLI.Options{args: [], command: "alice", path: ".", switches: %{debug: true}, unknown_args: [], unknown_switches: []}

Returns the scope for the given line as a tuple consisting of the call to
define the scope (`:defmodule`, `:def`, `:defp` or `:defmacro`) and the
name of the scope.

Examples:

    {:defmodule, "Foo.Bar"}
    {:def, "Foo.Bar.baz"}

